==Making Guthix rest==
A high-intensity but profitable way to train Herblore is to make [[Guthix rest]], requiring 18 Herblore and partial completion of the [[One Small Favour]] quest. Brewing Guthix rest differs from other methods of training the skill, as care must to be taken to not misclick and add too many herbs to the [[Herb tea mix|partially-complete tea]]; doing so grants no experience and ruins the tea. It also requires the player to click on each and every ingredient, as unlike brewing potions and cleaning herbs, subsequent teas are not automatically made after making just one of them. These two factors combined make this a very intensive method of training. Players should note that the [[amulet of chemistry]] has no effect when brewing Guthix rest. 

Brewing the tea is done in four steps, granting 14, 14.5, 15, and 15.5 experience for each step, for a total of 59 experience for each tea completed. The player must add 2 [[guam]], 1 [[marrentill]], and 1 [[harralander]], in any order, to a [[cup of hot water]]. Adding too many herbs will ruin the tea, granting no experience for the failed step and resulting in a worthless [[ruined herb tea]]. 

With moderate to high concentration it is possible to make around 800 cups of 3-dose Guthix rest per hour, costing {{Coins|{{GEP|Cup of hot water|800}}+{{GEP|Guam leaf|1600}}+{{GEP|Marrentill|800}}+{{GEP|Harralander|800}}}}. This results in 47,200 Herblore experience gained. Players should combine the teas into 4-dose variants at [[Bob Barter (herbs)|Bob Barter]] at the [[Grand Exchange]] before selling. Selling 600 4-dose teas will result in a net profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Guthix rest(4)|800}}*0.75-({{GEP|Cup of hot water|800}}+{{GEP|Guam leaf|1600}}+{{GEP|Marrentill|800}}+{{GEP|Harralander|800}})}}. This equals out to {{Coins|({{GEP|Guthix rest(4)|0.75}}-({{GEP|Cup of hot water}}+{{GEP|Guam leaf|2}}+{{GEP|Marrentill}}+{{GEP|Harralander}}))/59}} profit per experience for a completed tea.

